- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper proposes a new method for numerical solution of partial differential equations, specifically for wave and diffusion problems. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The proposed method has potential applications in various fields of engineering and science where wave and diffusion problems arise. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper introduces a new mathematical tool, the RBF wavelet series, for solving partial differential equations. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper may involve the development of algorithms for implementing the RBF wavelet series. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): This category is less likely, but the paper may have applications in modeling and analyzing diffusion processes in social networks.
